text:
Definitely one of the better noodle stalls in the area. Texture is just right. Vinegar+black sauce combo is the classic "Mee Pok" flavour of the old days.

Item 1 on the menu is an interesting pork soup kway teow with intestines. Good (unless you're averse to that kind of stuff).
My favourite kuay teow tng and dried noodle place. Fresh ingredients and tasty soup.

The order was delicious!!! I was injured and sick so I ordered the spinach soup but I cannot eat meat. I wrote in the remarks and the seller did follow exactly the instructions and the beehoon was so delicious, not plain tasting. Do support!!! ‚ù§Ô∏èüíØ
